<item>
            <title>[LU-14907] VM_WRITE should not trigger layout write</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14907</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;VM area marked with VM_WRITE means that pages may be written, but mmap page write may ne ver happen.&lt;br/&gt;
It should delay layout write until the actual modification on the file happen in -&amp;gt;page_mkwrite().&lt;br/&gt;
Otherwise, it will trigger panic for PCC-RO sanity-pcc test_21f().&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fixes: f2d1c4ee4 (&quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14647&quot; title=&quot;mapwrite a FLR file does not stale other mirrors&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-14647&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-14647&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; flr: mmap write/punch does not stale other mirrors&quot;)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
